cs.HC, cs.WEB, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.SI 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) - The paper focuses on measuring human perception of web page load time, which is a key aspect of HCI. 
2. cs.WEB (Web Technologies) - The paper discusses new protocols and content delivery mechanisms for improving webpage load time, which falls under the scope of web technologies. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions the impact of online advertisements on user experience, which can involve multimedia content. 
4. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper involves collecting and analyzing data from web users, which can be related to information retrieval. 
5. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper involves crowdsourcing measurements from a large number of participants, which can be related to social and information networks.
